道(dào)(4) 　“a destiny, a state of existence (of sentient beings)”　<span class="xr">Cf. <a href="bword://惡道">惡道</a>(è dào), <a href="bword://禽獸道">禽獸道</a>(qín shòu dào), <a href="bword://人道">人道</a>(rén dào), <a href="bword://三惡道">三惡道</a>(sān è dào); </span><p style="margin-left:3em; text-indent:-2em;">Lk. 470a9.菩薩終不還<span style="color: #8B0000">道</span><span style="color: #8B0000">道</span>，會當得佛，終不歸三惡道。是菩薩未曾離諸佛時。(p)</p><p style="margin-left:3em; text-indent:-1em;">AS. 234.2 = R. 473.13 = AAA. 890.15..<i>anya~ gati</i>~ (“[No] other destiny [except full enlightenment can be expected of him.]” [AsP.tr.II  273 = AsP.tr.  196]); ZQ. 503b10 = Lk ; not found at  Zfn. ; Kj. 579b5.(不生)餘處; not found at  Xz(I). 859b25.; not found at  Xz(II). 920b7.; not found at  Sh. 667a5.; Tib.Pk. 279a3 = D. 257a6..<i>’gro ba gzhan</i>; </p>

